INSERT INTO course_chunks (class_id, source, topic_tag, content) VALUES (1, 'lecture', 'Link Analysis for Web Search', 'hub scores • Normalize auth scores • (skip in this example) 39 I love pizza I love EECS 485 I love the projects in EECS 485 I wonder which EECS classes I should take next semester This is not a PageRank question H = 3 A = 0 H = 3 A = 0 H = 2 A = 3 H = 5 A = 0 H = 0 A = 2 HITS example • Update authority scores • A page is a good authority if it is pointed-to by many good hubs 40 I love pizza I love EECS 485 I love the projects in EECS 485 I wonder which EECS classes I should take next semester This is not a PageRank question H = 3 A = 0 H = 3 A = 0 H = 2 A = 11 H = 5 A = 0 H = 0 A = 7 HITS example • Update hub scores • A page is a good hub if it points to many good authorities 41 I love pizza I love EECS 485 I love the projects in EECS 485 I wonder which EECS classes I should take next semester This is not a Page ank question H = 11 A = 0 H = 11 A = 0 H = 7 A = 11 H = 18 A = 0 H = 0 A = 7 HITS example • HITS continues until convergence • Stop this example after 2 rounds 42 I love pizza I love EECS 485 I love the projects in EECS 485 I wonder which EECS classes I should take next semester This is not a PageRank question H = 11 A = 0 H = 11 A = 0 H = 7 A = 11 H = 18 A = 0 H = 0 A = 7 HITS vs. PageRank • HITS is dependent on the query • You need the query to build the root set and base set • PageRank is query-independent • One considers the links between pages, nothing else • Compute it once and save the result • Scores from either/both algorithms can be combined with Vector model tf-idf similarity score 43 Agenda • Document importance • Link-based ranking algorithms • PageRank algorithm • HITS algorithm • Search engine optimization 44 Search engine optimization • Search engine optimization: techniques to increase the visibility of your page in search engine results • Example 1: You have a personal web page. You want your web page to be the top hit when someone searches for your name. • Example 2: Most users don''t look beyond first page of search results. If your business appears on the first page, more clicks. More clicks -> more business. 45 Keywords • TF x IDF is one factor in search rankings • How can you influence TF x IDF? 46 Keywords • TF x IDF is one factor in search rankings • What can you do to influence');
INSERT INTO course_chunks (class_id, source, topic_tag, content) VALUES (1, 'lecture', 'Link Analysis for Web Search', 'once and save the result • Scores from either/both algorithms can be combined with Vector model tf-idf similarity score 43 Agenda • Document importance • Link-based ranking algorithms • PageRank algorithm • HITS algorithm • Search engine optimization 44 Search engine optimization • Search engine optimization: techniques to increase the visibility of your page in search engine results • Example 1: You have a personal web page. You want your web page to be the top hit when someone searches for your name. • Example 2: Most users don''t look beyond first page of search results. If your business appears on the first page, more clicks. More clicks -> more business. 45 Keywords • TF x IDF is one factor in search rankings • How can you influence TF x IDF? 46 Keywords • TF x IDF is one factor in search rankings • What can you do to influence TF x IDF? • Pages focus on a particular topic • You''ll probably naturally use important (relevant) words multiple times • Length won''t help you (remember normalization?) • Create a page with many repetitions of keywords • Search engines hate this. They "spam" filter for it. 47 Keyword technical considerations • Search engine needs text to extract keywords • Use text rather than images for important content • Is your name in a banner image? Is it also in the text? • Site should work with JavaScript disabled • Some search engines use a JavaScript rendering engine on some pages, but don''t count on it. 48 Links • PageRank is another factor in search rankings • What can you do to influence PageRank? 49 Link spam • Bots add comments to blogs. Comments link back to your site. • Blog owner should use rel="nofollow" attribute for links in comments. Search engines then ignore these links. • Search engines detect and filter this as spam. 50 Link technical considerations • The more legit links to your site the better • Avoid links that look like form queries • • Use different links for different pages • Think about how wolverine access works. You click a link, and the URL doesn''t change! Don''t do this. 51 Other relevance factors • Google says, “Relevancy is determined by over 200 factors, one of which is the PageRank for a given page.” 52 Next time • Last time we used the words on a page to rank search results • Rank on document content • Today we used the links between web pages to improve search results • Rank on document importance • Next time we''ll cover speed and scaling 53');
